<p>I love bitcoin. I think it has enormous potential to replace state currencies, which means freedom from robbery.<br />
Mt.Gox is a primary exchanger. Some government, unnamed, has put pressure on them to seize funds from those who have made deposits.<br />
A &#8220;verification&#8221; of identity, to include utility bills, passport and driver&#8217;s license, is required to access your funds, AFTER a deposit has been made.<br />
Reputedly, even providing these documents does not result in a refund.<br />
I wonder which government might do that! hahaha.<br />
They got thirty dollars from me, never to be seen again.<br />
Use Tradehill or the Bitcoin market.<br />
Glenn</p>
